  "instructions": [
    "Preheat pressure cooker to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Season the salmon fillets with caraway seeds, salt, and pepper.",
    "In a pan, sauté the chopped onion and minced garlic until softened.",
    "Add the Dijon mustard, brown sugar, and lemon juice to the pan and stir to combine.",
    "Place the salmon fillets in the pressure cooker and pour the onion mixture over them.",
    "Cover the pressure cooker and cook for 8 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, mix the breadcrumbs and unsalted butter in a bowl.",
    "After 8 minutes, remove the salmon from the pressure cooker and top each fillet with the breadcrumb mixture.",
    "Return the salmon to the pressure cooker and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "Sprinkle with chopped fresh dill and grated nutmeg.",
    "Serve immediately.",
    "Let the salmon rest for 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
